<paragraph id="8B8E2B4AC7753371FF042809D543A26D" blockId="3.[151,1436,1482,2031]" box="[198,846,1562,1588]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
ADULT FEMALE (
<figureCitation id="130A37CFC7753371FE762809D7F7A26D" box="[436,506,1562,1588]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,255,1311,1335]" captionTargetBox="[434,1143,204,1255]" captionTargetId="figure-313@4.[402,1185,187,1295]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Adult female Eriococcus longisetosus Foldi &amp; Kozár sp. nov. Where A = dorsal macrotubular duct; B = microtubular duct: C = spinose seta; D = 5-locular pore; E = ventral macrotubular duct; F = long hair-like seta; G = metathoracic claw; H = short ventral seta; I = cruciform pore; J = antenna." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5096721" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5096721/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) described from 
<specimenCount id="9D37E0C3C7753371FD002809D547A26D" box="[706,842,1562,1588]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" type="generic">1 specimen</specimenCount>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8E2B4AC7753371FF042851D35FA28E" blockId="3.[151,1436,1482,2031]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="B945F758C7753371FF042851D788A205" bold="true" box="[198,389,1602,1628]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Mounted femal</emphasis>
e. Body outline elongate oval, 2.33 mm long, 1.37 mm wide. Antennae 7 segmented, each 
<quantity id="4CC986AFC7753371FF552879D6FDA2DD" box="[151,240,1642,1668]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.38" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" unit="mm" value="238.0">238 µm</quantity>
long; antennal segments with few hair-like setae, longest about 
<quantity id="4CC986AFC7753371FC192879D227A2DD" box="[987,1066,1642,1668]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.9" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" unit="mm" value="29.0">29 µm</quantity>
; segment III without setae; segment lengths (µm): I 43, II 43, III 49, IV 43, V 24, VI 24, and VII 6; apical segment with a long seta, 
<quantity id="4CC986AFC7753371FA852886D39AA2F6" box="[1351,1431,1685,1711]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.8" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" unit="mm" value="58.0">58 µm</quantity>
, plus three sensory falcate setae, each 
<quantity id="4CC986AFC7753371FD8F28AED4C8A28E" box="[589,709,1725,1751]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" metricValueMax="2.7" metricValueMin="2.1" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" unit="mm" value="24.0" valueMax="27.0" valueMin="21.0">21–27 µm</quantity>
long. Frontal lobes absent. Eyes near margin on venter.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8E2B4AC7753371FF0428F6D5B9A3B6" blockId="3.[151,1436,1482,2031]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis id="B945F758C7753371FF0428F6D700A2A6" bold="true" box="[198,269,1765,1791]" pageId="3" pageNumber="54">Vente</emphasis>
r. Labium 3-segmented, 
<quantity id="4CC986AFC7753371FDEF28F6D484A2A6" box="[557,649,1765,1791]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" unit="mm" value="120.0">120 µm</quantity>
long. Legs well developed. Prothoracic legs (lengths in µm): coxa 106, trochanter + femur 256, tibia 134, tarsus 129. Mesothoracic legs (lengths in µm): coxa 96, trochanter + femur 262, tibia 144, tarsus 146. Metathoracic legs (lengths in µm): coxa 118, trochanter + femur 272, tibia 161, tarsus 140, tarsal digitules knobbed, each 59, claw 51, claw digitules each 53, slightly knobbed. Metathoracic coxae with 110–120 large translucent pores; femur with about 14–21 translucent pores dorsally at distal end; trochanter with two sensory pores on each side; claw with a denticle. Legs with few hair-like setae, trochanteral seta longest 
<quantity id="4CC986AFC7753371FE7929C6D45FA3B6" box="[443,594,2005,2031]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.275" metricValueMax="1.3" metricValueMin="1.25" pageId="3" pageNumber="54" unit="mm" value="127.5" valueMax="130.0" valueMin="125.0">125–130 µm</quantity>
, tarsus with one sensory pore.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF4E7BC2C7723376FF552B0CD58AA125" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5096721" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5096721" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5096721/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" startId="4.[151,255,1311,1335]" targetBox="[434,1143,204,1255]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="8B8E2B4AC7723376FF552B0CD58AA125" blockId="4.[151,1436,1311,1404]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="B945F758C7723376FF552B0CD717A16E" bold="true" box="[151,282,1311,1335]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">FIGURE 2.</emphasis>
Adult female 
<taxonomicName id="4C3150C9C7723376FE032B33D561A16E" authority="Foldi &amp; Kozar" authorityName="Foldi &amp; Kozar" authorityYear="2007" box="[449,876,1312,1335]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longisetosus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B945F758C7723376FE032B33D4C8A16E" box="[449,709,1312,1335]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">Eriococcus longisetosus</emphasis>
Foldi &amp; Kozár
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A2764A23C7723376FCB62B0CD5C6A16E" box="[884,971,1311,1335]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" rank="species">
<emphasis id="B945F758C7723376FCB62B0CD5C8A16E" bold="true" box="[884,965,1311,1335]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">sp. nov</emphasis>
.
</taxonomicNameLabel>
Where A = dorsal macrotubular duct; B = microtubular duct: C = spinose seta; D = 5-locular pore; E = ventral macrotubular duct; F = long hair-like seta; G = metathoracic claw; H = short ventral seta; I = cruciform pore; J = antenna.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8B8E2B4AC7723376FF042BA3D59AA2E3" blockId="4.[151,1436,1456,2002]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">
Disc pores each with 5 loculi and 
<quantity id="4CC986AFC7723376FDA02BA3D4AFA193" box="[610,674,1456,1482]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 µm</quantity>
in diameter, distributed in bands on posterior 4 abdominal segments and scattered elsewhere on rest of abdomen, thorax and head. Peritremes of anterior spiracles each 
<quantity id="4CC986AFC7723376FABD2BCBD6B2A243" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.3" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="43.0">43 µm</quantity>
wide. Long hair-like setae: longest up to about 
<quantity id="4CC986AFC7723376FD312813D587A243" box="[755,906,1536,1562]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.325" metricValueMax="1.35" metricValueMin="1.3" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="132.5" valueMax="135.0" valueMin="130.0">130–135 µm</quantity>
long, distributed mainly on median and submedian regions; shorter setae, each 
<quantity id="4CC986AFC7723376FDF8283BD4BEA21B" box="[570,691,1576,1602]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.4" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="27.0" valueMax="30.0" valueMin="24.0">24–30 µm</quantity>
long, in a submarginal band. Microtubular duct absent. Macrotubular ducts of one size, each about 
<quantity id="4CC986AFC7723376FD972843D4BCA233" box="[597,689,1616,1642]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4 µm</quantity>
wide and 
<quantity id="4CC986AFC7723376FCED2843D5A7A233" box="[815,938,1616,1642]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.35" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="13.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="12.0">12–15 µm</quantity>
long, with inner ductule about 
<quantity id="4CC986AFC7723376FAE02843D391A233" box="[1314,1436,1616,1642]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="1.2" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="13.0" valueMax="14.0" valueMin="12.0">12–14 µm</quantity>
long: sparse throughout. Sessile pores each 
<quantity id="4CC986AFC7723376FD60286BD4ECA2CB" box="[674,737,1656,1682]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 µm</quantity>
wide, mostly in a sparse submarginal band, absent on last three abdominal segments. Anal lobes each with 3 hair-like setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8E2B4AC7723376FF0428DBD2EDA36B" blockId="4.[151,1436,1456,2002]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="B945F758C7723376FF0428DBD729A2BB" bold="true" box="[198,292,1736,1762]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">Margin</emphasis>
. Ventral marginal spinose setae similar to those on dorsum but slightly smaller, sparsely distributed along margin as follows: with a small group on head, with a total of about 7 on thoracic segments, and with 2 spinose setae on abdomen; absent from margins of posterior four abdominal segments.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B8E2B4AC7723377FF042953D50CA573" blockId="4.[151,1436,1456,2002]" lastBlockId="5.[151,1436,152,698]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="56" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">
<emphasis id="B945F758C7723376FF042953D726A303" bold="true" box="[198,299,1856,1882]" pageId="4" pageNumber="55">Dorsum</emphasis>
. Dorsal spinose setae each 
<quantity id="4CC986AFC7723376FDB02953D4E6A303" box="[626,747,1856,1882]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.85" metricValueMax="7.6" metricValueMin="4.1" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="58.5" valueMax="76.0" valueMin="41.0">41–76 µm</quantity>
long, abundant in a dense group on head, in a broad band on each thoracic segment, and in a transverse segmental band 2–3 setae wide on each abdominal segment but absent from segment VIII. Macrotubular ducts each 
<quantity id="4CC986AFC7723376FCE02983D579A3F3" box="[802,884,1936,1962]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="25.0">25 µm</quantity>
long and 
<quantity id="4CC986AFC7723376FC3A2983D254A3F3" box="[1016,1113,1936,1962]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="5.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="5.0">5–6 µm</quantity>
wide, sparsely distributed throughout. Microtubular ducts each 
<quantity id="4CC986AFC7723376FD8829ABD485A38B" box="[586,648,1976,2002]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="55" unit="mm" value="5.0">5 µm</quantity>
long, scattered among dorsal setae and a microtubular duct present near each dorsal spinose seta. Disc pores absent. Anal ring with 8 hair-like setae, each about 
<quantity id="4CC986AFC7733377FB382E8BD35AA4EB" box="[1274,1367,152,178]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.28" pageId="5" pageNumber="56" unit="mm" value="128.0">128 µm</quantity>
long. Anal lobes about as long as wide, membranous, each with two spinose setae along outer margin and one spinose seta on inner margin, similar to those on dorsum; each apical seta on anal lobe about 
<quantity id="4CC986AFC7733377FB7E2EFBD31AA55B" box="[1212,1303,232,258]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.1" pageId="5" pageNumber="56" unit="mm" value="210.0">210 µm</quantity>
long. Suranal setae hair-like. Median sclerotised plate absent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32B78C1C7733377FF042F24D5ACA523" pageId="5" pageNumber="56" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8B8E2B4AC7733377FF042F24D5ACA523" blockId="5.[151,1436,152,698]" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis id="B945F758C7733377FF042F24D746A508" bold="true" box="[198,331,311,337]" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">Etymology</emphasis>
. The species epithet is derived from the Latin 
<emphasis id="B945F758C7733377FCA42F2BD5B9A508" box="[870,948,312,337]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">longus</emphasis>
meaning long and 
<emphasis id="B945F758C7733377FB502F2BD2CCA508" box="[1170,1217,312,337]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">seta</emphasis>
meaning bristle or hair, referring to the exceptionally long setose setae on the venter.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32B78C1C7733377FF042F94D30CA5FB" box="[198,1281,391,418]" pageId="5" pageNumber="56" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8B8E2B4AC7733377FF042F94D30CA5FB" blockId="5.[151,1436,152,698]" box="[198,1281,391,418]" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis id="B945F758C7733377FF042F94D421A5F8" bold="true" box="[198,556,391,417]" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">Distribution and Host plants</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B945F758C7733377FDF82F94D49DA5F8" bold="true" box="[570,656,391,417]" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">
<collectingCountry id="F3266BDAC7733377FDF82F94D486A5F8" box="[570,651,391,417]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">Brazil</collectingCountry>
:
</emphasis>
<collectingRegion id="49F5E5A8C7733377FD5A2F9BD578A5FB" box="[664,885,392,418]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3150C9C7733377FC432F9BD243A5F8" box="[897,1102,392,417]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Annona" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="56" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="muricata">
<emphasis id="B945F758C7733377FC432F9BD243A5F8" box="[897,1102,392,417]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">Annona muricata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C3150C9C7733377FB9F2F9BD2F8A5FB" box="[1117,1269,392,418]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="56" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Annonaceae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C32B78C1C7733377FF042FBCD565A6E3" pageId="5" pageNumber="56" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B8E2B4AC7733377FF042FBCD565A6E3" blockId="5.[151,1436,152,698]" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">
<emphasis id="B945F758C7733377FF042FBCD74FA590" bold="true" box="[198,322,431,457]" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">Comment</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C3150C9C7733377FEA62FA3D411A590" authorityName="Foldi &amp; Kozar" authorityYear="2007" box="[356,540,432,457]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longisetosus">
<emphasis id="B945F758C7733377FEA62FA3D411A590" box="[356,540,432,457]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">E. longisetosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from all other known species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3150C9C7733377FBDD2FA3D2AEA590" authorityName="Targioni Tozzetti" authorityYear="1868" box="[1055,1187,432,457]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B945F758C7733377FBDD2FA3D2AEA590" box="[1055,1187,432,457]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">Eriococcus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having abundant strong, long hair-like setae medially on venter of all segments. There are some similarities with 
<taxonomicName id="4C3150C9C7733377FACA2FCBD742A643" authority="(Hempel, 1900)" baseAuthorityName="Hempel" baseAuthorityYear="1900" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Annona" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="56" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="perplexus">
<emphasis id="B945F758C7733377FACA2FCBD391A5A8" box="[1288,1436,472,497]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">A. perplexus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFA056BBC7733377FF5D2C13D74AA643" author="Hempel, A." box="[159,327,512,538]" pageId="5" pageNumber="56" pagination="365 - 537" refId="ref8176" refString="Hempel, A. (1900) As Coccidas Brazileiras. Revista do Museu Paulista, Sao Paulo, 4, 365 - 537." type="journal article" year="1900">Hempel, 1900</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3150C9C7733377FE452C13D4FFA643" authority="(Morrison, 1919)" baseAuthorityName="Morrison" baseAuthorityYear="1919" box="[391,754,512,538]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Annona" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="56" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jorgenseni">
<emphasis id="B945F758C7733377FE452C13D42FA640" box="[391,546,512,537]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">A. jorgenseni</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFA056BBC7733377FDF32C13D4E7A643" author="Morrison, H." box="[561,746,512,538]" pageId="5" pageNumber="56" pagination="63 - 91" refId="ref8673" refString="Morrison, H. (1919) A report on Coccidae from Argentina, with description of apparently new species (Hom.). Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 21, 63 - 91." type="journal article" year="1919">Morrison, 1919</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in the arrangement of the dorsal spines and the large number of pores on each posterior coxa (110–120). However, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3150C9C7733377FC992C3BD21DA618" authorityName="Foldi &amp; Kozar" authorityYear="2007" box="[859,1040,552,577]" class="Insecta" family="Eriococcidae" genus="Eriococcus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="56" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longisetosus">
<emphasis id="B945F758C7733377FC992C3BD21DA618" box="[859,1040,552,577]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">E. longisetosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C3150C9C7733377FB772C3BD341A618" baseAuthorityName="Hempel" baseAuthorityYear="1900" box="[1205,1356,552,577]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Annona" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="56" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="perplexus">
<emphasis id="B945F758C7733377FB772C3BD341A618" box="[1205,1356,552,577]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">E. perplexus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the absence of frontal lobes, and in the large size of the coxal pores. It differs from 
<taxonomicName id="4C3150C9C7733377FBF52C43D2DFA630" baseAuthorityName="Morrison" baseAuthorityYear="1919" box="[1079,1234,592,617]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Annona" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="56" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jorgenseni">
<emphasis id="B945F758C7733377FBF52C43D2DFA630" box="[1079,1234,592,617]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">E. jorgenseni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the absence of cruciform pores on the most posterior abdominal segments of the venter, and in having many fewer (0–2) ventral submarginal spinose setae (3–5 present on 
<taxonomicName id="4C3150C9C7733377FD7E2CB3D55BA6E0" baseAuthorityName="Morrison" baseAuthorityYear="1919" box="[700,854,672,697]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Annonaceae" genus="Annona" kingdom="Plantae" order="Magnoliales" pageId="5" pageNumber="56" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jorgenseni">
<emphasis id="B945F758C7733377FD7E2CB3D55BA6E0" box="[700,854,672,697]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="56">E. jorgenseni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
